---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About · a → b">
  <h1 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold">About</h1>

  <div class="space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed">
    <p>
      a → b is a free file converter that does one thing: convert files from format
      <em>a</em> to format <em>b</em>, in your browser, without ever sending your data anywhere.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">How is this free?</h2>
    <p>
      It costs us almost nothing to run. The site is static HTML and JavaScript hosted on
      Cloudflare's free tier. Conversion happens on your device, so we don't pay for servers to
      process your files. We don't sell your data. We don't show ads. If you'd like to support the
      project, you can
      <a
        href="https://ko-fi.com/rosscyking"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        class="underline hover:no-underline">buy me a coffee</a
      >. Optional, never asked twice.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Why does this exist?</h2>
    <p>
      Most online file converters upload your files to their servers. Even when they say they don't
      keep them, you have to take their word for it. We wanted a tool we could trust with personal
      documents — contracts, tax forms, scanned IDs — without that leap of faith.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Open source</h2>
    <p>
      The code is on
      <a
        href="https://github.com/rosscyking1115/a-to-b"
        class="underline hover:no-underline"
        rel="noopener">GitHub</a
      >. Anyone can audit it.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
